posts_info.description: Give your sneakers a unique twist! We love the chocolate brown on these Nike Dunk Low 'Cacao Wow' sneakers, along with coconut milk base color.  We’re also seeing a lot of pairs getting the ageing treatment on the midsole, as seen here, giving it a vintage vibe. We wanted to add another layer of chocolate by selecting a cool tone light brown rope. This twisting lacing technique also gives the shoe a little more dimension. What we swapped: — Light Brown Thick Rope in 53” Music: — De@d Man Walking x One Call Away mashup by @raymonddeejay #loopedlaces #getloopedin #laceswap #lacingtutorial #sneaker

Say goodbye to boring laces Like the previous collaboration pairs, these Air Jordan 1 Low Travis Scott ‘Olive’ sneakers keep the colorway pretty neutral with more earthy tones.  We wanted to make a big impression so chose a bright, bold color lace to draw some attention. We used a reverse-lacing technique where the laces go from the outside inward, which keep the simplicity but give the laces more volume. What we swapped: — Union Gold Flat Laces in 59” Music: — Sunshine x Sexy Love mashup by @DJ Playboi Pocky  #loopedlaces #getloopedin #laceswap #lacingtutorial #sneaker

You gotta lace me the right way We love the soft nubuck on these Nike Dunk Fossil Rose sneakers and wanted to play up the subtle colorway with a perfect pastel pink that’s sure to get you blushing. We used the top-down lacing technique to create a no-tie look that’s clean and simple at the top of the sneaker.  What we swapped: — Blush Flat Laces in 59” Music: — Genie In a Bottle afrobeats mix by @happi.music #loopedlaces #getloopedin #laceswap #lacingtutorial #sneaker

Drum roll for sneaker royalty 🥁👑  These Air Jordan 1 High 'Royal Reimagined' sneakers showcase the intersection between old and new, with its classic Jordan design and iconic royal blue colorway, upgraded by a new suede material used for the construction of the shoe.  With this pair, the details are minor but mighty - with the use of different textures of suede on the entire shoe's surface, giving it more dimension. It was only suitable that we used our most premium lace option on a pair like this, opting for a waxed lace with thoughtful details like embrossed black metal aglets to provide some weight for the no-tie method.  What we swapped: — Black Waxed Laces in 59" Music: — Drums (original: Like I Love You) drum rendition by @thestickmenproject #loopedlaces #getloopedin #laceswap #lacingtutorial #sneaker

Let's your laces WOW people The Nike Dunk Low 'Cacao Wow' is definitely a unique pair with its brown and coconut milk colorway. This pair brings togethers the richness from a chocolate hue, contrasted by a light and creamy off-white, with a sail midsole as the final touch. We really wanted to wow people with this sneaker so added our biggest, brightest JUMBO lace for a vibrant pop of color. We also used the reverse-lacing technique (lacing from the outside of the eyelet in) for maximum lace exposure.  What we swapped: — Light Pink Jumbo Rope in 53" Music: — Just Wanna Rock x I Know What U Want mashup by @raymonddeejay #loopedlaces #getloopedin #laceswap #lacingtutorial #sneaker

posts_info.description: Sleeper Sneaker Collection 💪👟 *FOLLOW if you’re a collector! #fyp #foryou #yyc #hypebeast #sneakerhead #streetwear

How To Avoid Overpaying For Sneakers ❌👟 *do you CHECK MARKET VALUE? Due to the highly volatile market that exists for sneakers - the price for a single pair can change overnight. Due to this, it may be easy for unaware buyers to overpay. You can find the current market value for a pair by searching up the most recent sale prices for it on your favourite selling platforms. It is recommended that you know the value of a pair so that you don’t overpay - many resell shops mark up prices by over 200% so knowing this can definitely save you money! #LearnOnTikTok #foryou #yyc #hypebeast #sneakerhead #reseller

How To Buy High-Value Sneakers 👟📈 *do you INSPECT BEFORE PURCHASE?  When buying sneakers from the secondary market, it’s important to know exactly what you’re getting. Sneakers only retain their full value when they are deadstock and have all the original parts. (DS + OG ALL) Resellers almost always maximize profit margins, therefore as a buyer you need to know the true value of a sneaker. When buying personal pairs, I try to fond non-DS pairs to save money - highly encourage you to do the same. #LearnOnTikTok #foryou #yyc #hypebeast #sneakerhead #reseller

Red Flags When Selling Sneakers 🚩👟 *have you SEEN THESE ONLINE SCAMMERS?  The sneaker buying and selling marketplace deals with high value transactions - as a result this has created potential risks for both buyers and sellers. As a seller, oftentimes scammers will purchase your item and then attempt to fraudulently request a refund. You need to do everything you can to avoid loses against these scams. Here are some red flags to watch for: off-site transactions, lack of communication and switching billing/shipping addresses. #LearnOnTikTok #foryou #yyc #hypebeast #sneakerhead #reseller
